metadata.name: AS AB0VE \\\ S0 BEL0W
metadata.description:
Point Pleasant Police Department  
Evidence inventory: October 9th, 1999

Evidence Item #1  
1966-121366-057  
Damaged VHS video footage — charred casing, internal film noticeably heat damaged; contents incoherent.  Scotch tape label reads, “AS ABOVE SO BELOW.”  

Evidence Item #2  
1966-121366-058  
Unmarked journal — entry dated December 9th, 1966  
”…they aren’t what they seem  
….they aren’t what they seem  
….they aren’t what they seem  
….they aren’t what they seem

He says I shouldn’t say anything.  
I can’t hold onto this anymore.”

END OF PHYSICAL EVIDENCE

Other journal contents incoherent or illegible.

Eyewitness testimony — Neighbor says they saw a man screaming from the second floor window when the fire started.  After thorough investigation, no human remains were found.  The family that owns the home was in Florida at the time of the incident and says the home was vacant.

SUMMARY:  Case closed after detectives determined the fire was caused by a gas leak.  Evidence dated and unrelated to ongoing investigation.  

APPROVED FOR DISPOSAL
